Φ(EpistemicGames) = σ(metacognition|frameworks) ∘ ρ(sensemaking|gap-detection) ∘ λ(construction|iteration) ∘ β(fluency|growth) ∘ δγ(knowledge|practice) ∘ μ(structure|transferability) + ε | :epistemic_fluency

; === Operator Breakdown ===

; σ — Air / Aerunik (0.85)
;   Metacognitive awareness of one's own epistemic stance and frameworks in play.
;   The learner becomes aware not just of what they know, but how they know it —
;   which epistemic game they are playing, which moves are available, and which
;   frameworks structure their reasoning. Aerunik governs the clarity of seeing
;   one's own cognitive weather patterns.

; ρ — Water / Sentaria (0.78)
;   Sensemaking as relational flow: detecting gaps and seeking coherence through
;   empathic engagement. The sensemaking epistemic game begins when a learner
;   perceives a gap between what they understand and what they need to explain.
;   Sentaria governs the felt sense of incoherence that drives inquiry forward.

; λ — Fire / Jvalion (0.82)
;   Active knowledge construction through iterative explanation-building and game
;   moves. Rather than absorbing transmitted knowledge, the learner builds explanations
;   through repeated cycles of proposing, testing, and refining. Jvalion fuels the
;   generative drive — the impulse to construct rather than receive.

; β — Wood / Arboriel (0.70)
;   Epistemic fluency as organic growth across multiple ways of knowing. Over time,
;   exposure to multiple epistemic games cultivates fluency — the ability to shift
;   between knowledge-construction strategies as context demands. Arboriel nurtures
;   this branching development of cognitive repertoire.

; δγ — Earth / Humavita (0.65)
;   Grounding abstract epistemology in embodied educational practice and community.
;   Epistemic games are not merely theoretical — they require classroom enactment,
;   peer interaction, and material contexts. Humavita provides the stable substrate
;   where abstract games become lived pedagogical practice.

; μ — Metal / Ferrosid (0.72)
;   Structural transferability of epistemic game patterns across domains. The game
;   structures (mapping, modeling, physical mechanism games) form reusable templates
;   that can be applied from physics to philosophy to political resistance. Ferrosid
;   encodes the durable architecture of these transferable patterns.

; === Z-State ===
; Epistemic fluency — the learner navigates multiple knowledge-construction
; strategies fluidly, shifting between epistemic games as context requires,
; resistant to manipulation through meta-awareness of framing.

; === Tendency ===
; λ → 0.82 — The system leans toward active construction (fire). Knowledge is
; built, not received. The dominant mode is generative iteration.

# CE-STATE: flat
# EI-NOTE: No clear scale dominance identified
